{
  "texts": [
    "Batch correction is a crucial step for image-based profiling regardless of the feature space of choice.",
    "We hypothesized that a rich representation might encode both confounders and phenotypic features in a way that facilitates separating one type of variation from the other, i.e.",
    "disentangles the sources of variation.",
    "To test this, we evaluated how representations respond to the sphering transform, a linear transformation for batch correction based on singular value decomposition SVD (Methods).",
    "Sphering first finds directions of maximal variance in the set of control samples and then reverses their importance by inverting the eigenvalues."
  ]
}